[{"question":"Is it going too far?","answer":"I think it is.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":49,"aSentId":50},{"question":"How significant are these alleged gaffes be?","answer":"I think there have been more unforced errors than you would expect from a presidential campaign in the final months.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":59,"aSentId":60},{"question":"When Bill Clinton was fundraising, for example, would he often go harder on the rhetoric, thinking he was in a secure room with people that he could trust, or is this Mitt Romney\u0027s big fatal flaw, that he\u0027s been caught talking in a different way?","answer":"You have just got to assume, when you\u0027re in a presidential race, that every single moment is on the record.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":75,"aSentId":76},{"question":"If they had somebody like that, would they be doing better in the polls?","answer":"Well -- if you look back at that primary field that we were dealing with a year ago, watching in debates a year ago, there\u0027s no question with the exception perhaps of Rick Perry, who ended up imploding for other reasons, I don\u0027t think there was anybody else on that stage who could have gotten the nomination and been competitive in a presidential race.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":109,"aSentId":110},{"question":"What do you say to him?","answer":"You got nothing left to lose.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":120,"aSentId":121},{"question":"How is she doing, do you know?","answer":"You know, the transplant went as well, it\u0027s transfusion, really, went as well as can be expected.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":130,"aSentId":131},{"question":"I mean what\u0027s going on here?","answer":"No, I think what he was earlier saying is that the president was polling at 47 percent, still is.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":198,"aSentId":199},{"question":"You must have been incandescent, were you?","answer":"Two things.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":205,"aSentId":206},{"question":"Can you do it without increasing any taxation, because from where I sit, I just don\u0027t see that is a feasible position?","answer":"Well, I think you\u0027re going to have to increase taxes, Piers, on people who are very fortunate in this society, who are very wealthy.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":226,"aSentId":227},{"question":"What has he got to do to refocus, to re-galvanize and to try and get the right message over now to win this election?","answer":"Well, he needs to keep saying what he has been saying and force the press to focus on that.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":241,"aSentId":242},{"question":"Robert Reich, is there merit to what Grover Norquist is saying there?","answer":"I don\u0027t think there\u0027s very much merit, if any merit at all, Piers.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":254,"aSentId":255},{"question":"You must be worried, aren\u0027t you?","answer":"No.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":293,"aSentId":294},{"question":"Can I just -- can I just intervene here?","answer":"The Soviet Union was no more of a financial burden on America than Afghanistan and Iraq had been.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":317,"aSentId":318},{"question":"That\u0027s civil?","answer":"The fact of the matter is the Reagan recession was very deep, but it is nothing compared to what Barack Obama inherited from George W. Bush.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":337,"aSentId":338},{"question":"Has any president in the history of the United States ever handed a bigger financial crisis over to the guy that followed him than George Bush did?","answer":"Well, if you look at --","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":352,"aSentId":353},{"question":"Who?","answer":"Herbert Hoover.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":356,"aSentId":357},{"question":"Are you saying that FDR was the same as Herbert Hoover?","answer":"Well, he did -- Hoover took tax rates up to 75 percent from 25.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":361,"aSentId":362},{"question":"Isn\u0027t that a very similar position to what we\u0027re now seeing?","answer":"It\u0027s not, because the president just gave a speech about how the American people demanded Obamacare.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":372,"aSentId":373},{"question":"What do you make of it?","answer":"Not much of it good.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":421,"aSentId":422},{"question":"How much credence should we be giving it, do you think?","answer":"As to that part of it, plenty.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":426,"aSentId":427},{"question":"I wouldn\u0027t even have been aware of him being released?","answer":"No, he was in custody of the Defense Department.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":442,"aSentId":443},{"question":"It is just a collection of terrorist cells around the world?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s essentially a franchise.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":450,"aSentId":451},{"question":"Do you think that is plausible?","answer":"Sure, it\u0027s plausible.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":463,"aSentId":464},{"question":"Do you think there\u0027s any danger that he will be released at any stage, in any capacity?","answer":"UKASEY: I don\u0027t take a denial from the Justice Department as dispositive.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":474,"aSentId":475},{"question":"Final point I would make, do you believe from what we have seen in the last week, then, that America is once again under attack from al Qaeda?","answer":"America has always been under attack from al Qaeda.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":485,"aSentId":486},{"question":"Am I right?","answer":"That\u0027s correct.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":503,"aSentId":504},{"question":"I suppose the obvious question is how much can we expect to recover in the end?","answer":"ICARD: Well, we\u0027d like to think that we can recover all the 17.5 billion dollars.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":509,"aSentId":510},{"question":"Is that likely?","answer":"It depends on litigation.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":511,"aSentId":512},{"question":"Are you pleasantly encouraged by how far you\u0027ve come so far?","answer":"Oh, absolutely, because we started at zero.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":513,"aSentId":514},{"question":"Stephen, has Bernie Madoff been helpful at all in this process?","answer":"I would say no.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":530,"aSentId":531},{"question":"Is that right?","answer":"That\u0027s correct.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":537,"aSentId":538},{"question":"How would you categorize him?","answer":"ICARD: I really haven\u0027t thought about characterizing him at this point, because our efforts and our focus has been to go out and recover what we can, as much as we can, as quickly as we can, for the people for whom we are trying to get the best recoveries and best distribution.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":541,"aSentId":542},{"question":"This was the biggest Ponzi scheme in American history, right?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":543,"aSentId":544},{"question":"If you were to succeed in recovering the money, it would be the biggest recovery of its type that we would have ever seen?","answer":"Yes, of course.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":545,"aSentId":546},{"question":"He\u0027s pretty despicable human being, wasn\u0027t he?","answer":"I don\u0027t know that I would go that far, because, you know --","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":554,"aSentId":555},{"question":"Is that the maxim?","answer":"Well, that is true.","docId":"120920pmt","qSentId":569,"aSentId":570}]